node.text: Everyone wants the feeling of freedom, but procrastination can feel like you are caged and can't find the key. We all get stuck in patterns, and the patterns become habits. Procrastination is the same thing.  Procrastination is an action (or non-action) – and it does not define you. Why? It is a habit, that is a behavior pattern that can be changed into a new pattern

node.text:
People are like seedlings - we need to be nurtured and connected to nature, and our true nature, to grow. We invest a lot of time cultivating everything else: families, work, friends, and other interests. We look after them, prioritise them, and make time for them. The thing is, we won't flourish if we don't take time for ourselves, our self-care, our relaxation, our mental and physical health. We, through a lack of real effort stay alive, we may even grow but we will not truly thrive or bloom when we don’t take the time and water ourselves and give ourselves what we really need.

When we become a priority, life gets better. We feel better, have more energy and ability to help or support others. We are not pouring from an empty cup, our cup becomes overflowing. When we feel out of sorts, when we feel discomfort or discord there is a reason. Our life is communicating to us. Get curious, it is likely we are not taking the time we need to nurture ourselves. Action needs to be taken. What is it we need? What can we do to feel better? Time appears to be an obstacle, a reason, and an excuse for many people who do not take care of themselves. We all have the same amount of time in a day; the difference is how we prioritise it. If you take the time to water yourself, you will blossom.

Say YES if you are willing to take some time for yourself!

#wellnesswednesday

“There’s nowhere you can be that isn’t where you’re meant to be…” ― John Lennon

Have you noticed when you hope for something, it seldom occurs as you expect? However, the moment you surrender, it makes its way into your life with little worry. When a condition arises that does not match your mental picture, move into your heart and consider the greater lesson contained within the experience.

Trust that life supports your needs and will continue to do so as long as you maintain faith. Tap into your gratitude for your openness, your resourcefulness and your capacity to grow.  Don’t be attached to rigid outcomes. As the saying goes, “Trade your expectation for appreciation.” Life may not unfold how you imagine it, but believe in this benevolent force, regardless. Trust in the language of the heart and know that you are right where you need to be...

Give a Heart if you agree :)

"Books train your imagination to think big" - Taylor Swift

However you define yourself, whether you are an adult or a child, being exposed to new worlds, new perspectives, and new adventures blasts opens your mind. We see people trying find a better way of walking through the world, and introducing new ideas to ours.

node.text:
If you have a dream in your heart, know that it was given to YOU for a reason. It’s not anyone else’s dream - it’s yours. It resonates with you, otherwise it would not have come up. It is designed for you, was delivered through you, and must be stewarded by you. Think of yourself as a unique puzzle piece; without you, the puzzle of our humanity would not and could not be complete  So don’t let your mindset stop you before you even start. 

Instead take one step forward to find out more. Explore it, dream it, feel it. The phrase “wouldn’t it be cool if…” is a great way to try on your dream for size. Believe that you can take some steps; believe that you can learn as you go. You can figure it out, and pivot along the way. You are being invited to get into the flow of life. Trust that you are being guided and don’t ignore the whispers of your heart.

“If you choose to align with your source, with your spirit, then your life will go in a certain direction. If you choose to align yourself with your ego, and your false self, and the belief that who you are is what you accomplish and what other people think of you and what you accumulate, if you just go that route - the outer route, if you will, the outer path - your life will go in a different direction…Our greatest dreams are never out of reach, only out of belief.” - Wayne Dyer

#positivity
#quoteoftheday

We live in a comparison culture, and it’s easy to forget one essential piece of information. You are a miracle. To be here, you didn't have to do anything, you didn't have to win a competition, you didn't have to prove yourself to anyone or anything because chance decided that you were already good enough, and that counts for something.

Stop attempting to establish your worth by comparing yourself to others. There is no one who can compete with you, and no one compares to you.

You are already worthy because you are here on this planet right now.

node.text:
Did not being chosen for a job you desired even lead you to a better one? Did a breakup ever lead you to a better relationship? Sometimes we have rigid expectations of the path we are “supposed to be” on. Yet, life may have other ideas. 

Don't fight what comes up; instead, you can choose to go with the flow and see where it takes you. Life is usually pointing you in the direction of something greater. Examine yourself and realize that you already possess all you require to achieve. Don't fixate on what went wrong because you are already actually being guided to something better. Instead of dwelling too long in disappointment, ask yourself these  2 questions:

1. What have I learned from this situation? 

2.How can it make me stronger?

Trust and stay open; then you will notice the better things that are on the way.

Give a Heart if you have ever experienced this.

#quoteoftheday

node.text:
Everything that bothers you comes up for a reason. You have to ask yourself ‘why’ to get to the bottom of it. 

Consider that often what you don’t like or accept in yourself is precisely what irritates you in the other person. For example, if you witnessed a lot of anger when you were a child,  you may be uncomfortable with expressing anger now. So unconsciously, you may attract a partner who has anger issues, which can bother you a lot! Why do we do that? The relationship unknowingly becomes the playing ground for resolving old hurts.

And just as we have many emotions, we all have many sides, many different parts of ourselves. Some we can own (the “good “ parts), and some we disown or don’t want to admit. (These are sometimes called the split-off parts of ourselves or the shadow side.) 
 
What to do? Being willing to accept (and have compassion for) that part of yourself and skillfully learning, for example,  how to acknowledge and express your own anger, is a most positive step. 

AWARENESS -> SELF-ACCEPTANCE -> GROWTH

The emotions you are most uncomfortable with, may be the keys to helping you integrate all parts of yourself.  so you can finally feel at home in your own skin.

#thoughtfulthursday
#positivity
#quoteoftheday

node.text:
Sometimes growth does not happen in tandem, and when one person changes, it can disrupt the familiar rhythms of a relationship. That doesn’t have to spell disaster. It can be an invitation for the other person to grow as well. 

The only thing is... that is not in your control. If things devolve to full on stress and disrespect, it is important to know what works for you, and what crosses a line. There are times when taking a stand for yourself is the only way to move forward. Though, you cannot control how the other person will react, you can make choices that give you (and potentially both of you) the room to grow. 

 Remember you have a well of inner strength inside of you; realize how valuable and wonderful you are, and stay true to you. You alone have the power to decide who deserves your heart.

“No one can make you feel inferior without your consent.” - Eleanor Roosevelt

node.text:
Life is full of unexpected twists and turns; we really never know what will happen next. And when we think that life takes a turn for the worse, it’s so easy to succumb to disappointment and unhappiness. These are the moments when we are so preoccupied with the past and future that we forget to live in the here and now.

When we let go of the life we imagined, we can welcome whatever life brings us with open arms; which means we can focus on the things that we already have and the lives we already lead instead of on what we haven’t acquired or achieved.

When we let go of the image we imagined, life often opens far better doors for us to discover who we really are.

“Happiness is letting go of what you think your life is supposed to look like and celebrating it for everything that it is.” ~Mandy Hale

What is one thing you are willing to let go of?

#positivity
